## Source of truth

- Functional and technical requirements: @hw.md (Russian spec). Before changing behavior, align with it.

## Stack (non-negotiable)

- React 18+, TypeScript with **strict** typing (no weakening `strict` to “make it compile”).
- State: **Zustand** for app/auth/table state (e.g. sort persisted as required).
- UI: **Tailwind** for styling.
- Icons: **Lucide** only; when choosing icons, use the **suggest-lucide-icons** skill.

## Data & auth

- Products: [DummyJSON Products](https://dummyjson.com/docs/products) (list, loading states, search via API where required).
- Login: [DummyJSON Auth](https://dummyjson.com/docs/auth); show field-level or inline errors on API failure; “Создать” link is non-functional per spec.
- **Session persistence**: checkbox ON → persist token across browser restarts (e.g. `localStorage`); OFF → session ends when the **tab** closes (e.g. `sessionStorage` or equivalent).

## Homework-specific UI logic

- Rating **&lt; 3.5**: highlight in red.
- `refresh-ccw` (Lucide): refresh table data; `list-filter`: sort asc/desc with visible sort state (design at your discretion).
- Row actions menu (three dots in circle): **placeholder** only.
- “Add product”: form fields name, price, vendor, SKU; **no** real API save; **toast** on success.

## Browser

- Target latest **Google Chrome** for behavior and layout checks.